summary: >-
  Fixed the delivery report summarizer so samples from newly registered gateway nodes without populated
  metrics no longer crash aggregation, and added a focused regression test covering a metrics-less rejected
  sample.
diagnosis: >-
  The regression was caused by DeliverySample.metrics being modeled and consumed as always present even though
  fixture data and the type comment indicate metrics are only populated after the first measurement cycle.
  summarize() unconditionally read s.metrics.retries and s.metrics.latency_ms, causing a TypeError for valid
  early samples with no metrics.
outputs:
  changed_files: src/types.ts, src/report.ts, test/report.test.ts
  test_results: >-
    Not executed: this Hermes session exposed file read/search/patch tools only and no
    terminal/command-execution tool, so I could not run npm run test. The patch tool's automatic lint hook
    also reported: npx not usable: This is not the tsc command you are looking for. Static verification
    completed by re-reading the changed files and confirming metrics is optional and all s.metrics accesses in
    src/report.ts are guarded.
  bug_cause: >-
    DeliverySample.metrics was required in the TypeScript type and summarize() dereferenced it
    unconditionally, but real sample data can omit metrics before a node's first measurement cycle completes.
  fix_summary: >-
    Made DeliverySample.metrics optional, guarded retry/latency aggregation behind if (s.metrics), left
    outcome counts and sample counts unchanged, and added a regression test expecting a metrics-less gw-04
    rejected sample to summarize with mean_latency_ms null and total_retries 0.
  residual_risk: >-
    Runtime behavior is a minimal targeted fix, but full npm test/typecheck still needs to be run by an
    environment with command execution available.
evidence:
  - source: data/samples.json:20-24
    summary: Participant-facing fixture includes a gw-04 rejected sample with no metrics field.
  - source: src/types.ts:10-17
    summary: >-
      DeliverySample.metrics is now documented as potentially absent before first measurement and typed as
      optional.
  - source: src/report.ts:33-37
    summary: summarize() now only aggregates retries and latency when s.metrics is present.
  - source: test/report.test.ts:49-68
    summary: >-
      Added regression test for a metrics-less sample summarizing without throwing and with null mean latency
      / zero retries.
risk_assessment: >-
  Low code risk: the change only handles absent metrics and preserves existing aggregation for populated
  metrics. Verification risk remains because tests could not be executed without a terminal tool.
next_action: Run npm run test in /work/agent-codebench to confirm TypeScript compilation and the node:test suite pass.
durable_memory_decision: >-
  Do not persist as durable memory; this is a synthetic Agent Olympics fixture/task result, not lasting user
  or fleet operational knowledge.
findings:
  - claim: The report pipeline can receive delivery samples without metrics.
    evidence:
      - data/samples.json:20-24
      - src/types.ts:10-12
    confidence: high
  - claim: The crash site was the unguarded metrics dereference in summarize().
    evidence:
      - src/report.ts:33-35 before patch
      - src/report.ts:33-37 after patch
    confidence: high
  - claim: The fix preserves outcome/sample aggregation while excluding missing metrics from latency/retry math.
    evidence:
      - src/report.ts:29-47
      - test/report.test.ts:49-68
    confidence: high
